        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 2:03AM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 203 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ekalaka, moving northeast at 35 mph. Other storms may develop in the
same vicinity.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ekalaka, Medicine Rocks State Park, Webster, Willard and Mill Iron.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
